article.description: Ashley Sweat scored 16 of her 20 points in the second half to lead Kansas State to a 64-55 victory over Creighton.
article.headline: Sweat, Kansas State beat Creighton
article.linkText: Sweat lifts No. 18 K-State past Creighton
article.story:
MANHATTAN, Kan. -- Ashley Sweat scored 16 of her 20 points in the second half to lead Kansas State (No. 18 ESPN/USA Today, No. 25 AP) to a 64-55 victory over Creighton on Tuesday.

Marlies Gipson scored 14 points and blocked a season-high five shots and Kari Kincaid had 10 points for the Wildcats (8-0).

Chevelle Herring led Creighton (2-5) with 23 points. Kelsey Woodward added 15.

Herring made a jump shot in the lane to tie the score at 35 with about 15 minutes left, but Kincaid answered with a deep 3-pointer to give the Wildcats the lead for good.

Herring scored eight points in the first three minutes to lead the Bluejays to a 10-0 lead.

The advantage was 11 before the Wildcats used an 18-4 run to take a 20-17 lead with about six minutes left in the half. Gipson came up big during that stretch, scoring eight points, and Kansas State went into halftime leading 26-22.
